\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11692121 {\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 1.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And it came to pass after Isaac was old, that his eyes were dimmed so that he could not see; and he called Esau, his elder son, and said  to him, My son; and he said, Behold, I am here. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And he said, Behold, I am grown old, and know not the day of my death. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Now then  take thy weapons, both thy quiver and thy bow, and go into the plain, and get me venison,  }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 and make me meats, as I like them, and  bring them to me that I may eat, that my soul may bless thee, before I die. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Rebecca heard Isaac s
peaking to Esau his son; and  Esau went to the plain to procure venison for his father. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Rebecca said to Jacob her younger son, Behold, I heard thy father  speaking to Esau thy brother, saying, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Bring me venison, and prepare me meats, that I may eat and bless thee before the Lord before I  die. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Now then my son, hearken to me, as I command thee. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And go to the cattle and take for me thence two kids, tender and good,  and I will make them meats for thy father, as he likes. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And thou shalt bring them in to thy father, and he shall eat, that thy father may  bless thee before he dies. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Jacob said to his mother Rebecca, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I a smooth man. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  Peradventure my father may feel me, and I shall be before him as one ill intentioned, and I shall bring upon me a curse, and not a blessing.  }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And his mother said to him, On me be thy curse, son; only hearken to my voice, and go and bring them me. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  So he went and took  and brought them to his mo
ther; and his mother made meats, as his father liked them. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Rebecca having taken the fine raiment of  her elder son Esau which was with her in the house, put it on Jacob her  younger son. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And she put on his arms the skins of the kids,  and on the bare parts of his neck. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And she gave the meats, and the loaves which she had prepared, into the hands of Jacob her son.  }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And he brought them to his father, and said, Father; and he said, Behold I am here; who art thou, son?. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Jacob said to
 his  father, I, Esau thy first-born, have done as thou toldest me; rise, sit, and eat of my venison, that thy  soul may bless me. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Isaac said  to his son, What is this which thou hast quickly found? And he said, That which the Lord thy God presented before me. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Isaac  said to Jacob, Draw nigh to me, and I will feel thee, son, if thou art my son Esau or not. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 22.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Jacob drew nigh to his father Isaac, and  he felt him, and said, The voice is Jacob's voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 23.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And he knew him not, for his hands were as the  hands of his brother Esau, hairy; and he blessed him, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 24.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and he said, Art thou my son Esau? and he said, I am. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 25.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And he said, Bring  hither, and I will eat of thy venison, son, that my soul may bless 
thee; and he brought it near to him, and he ate, and he brought him wine,  and he drank. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 26.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Isaac his father said to him, Draw nigh to me, and kiss me, son. }
{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 27.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And he drew nigh and kissed him, and smelled  the smell of his garments, and blessed him, 
and said, Behold, the smell of my son is as the smell of an abundant field, which the Lord has  blessed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 28.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And may God give thee of the dew of heaven, and of the fatness of the earth and abundance of corn and wine. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 29.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And let  nations serve thee, and pr
inces bow down to thee, and be thou lord of thy brother, and the sons of thy father shall do thee reverence;  accursed is he that curses thee, and blessed is he that blesses thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 30.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And it came to pass after Isaac had ceased blessing his son Jacob,  it even came to pass, just when Jacob had gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came in from his hunting.  
}{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 31.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And he also had made meats and brought them to his father; and he said to his father, Let my father arise and eat of 
his son's venison,  that thy soul may bless me. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 32.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Isaac his father said to him, Who art thou? And he said, I am thy first-born son Esau. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 33.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Isaac  was amazed with very great amazement, and said, Who then is it that has procured venison for me an
d brought it to me? and I have eaten  of all before thou camest, and I have blessed him, and he shall be blessed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 34.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And it came to pass when Esau heard the words of his  father Isaac, he cried out with a great and very bitter cry, and said, Bless, I pray thee, me also, father. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 35.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And he said to him, Thy brother  has come with subtlety, and taken thy blessing. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 36.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And he said, Rightly was his name called Jacob, for lo! this second time has he  supplanted me; he has both taken my birthright and now he has taken my blessing; and Esau said to his father, Hast thou not left a blessing  for me, father? }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 37.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And Isaac answered and said to Esau, If I have made him thy lord, and have made all his brethren his servants, and  have strengthened him with corn and wine,
 what then shall I do for thee, son? }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 38.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Esau said to his father, Hast thou only one blessing  father? Bless, I pray thee, me also, father. And Isaac being troubled, Esau cried aloud and wept. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 39.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Isaac his father answered and  said to him, Behold, thy dwelling shall be of the fatness of the earth, and of the dew of heaven from above. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 40.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And thou shalt live by thy  sword, and shalt serve thy brother; and there shall be a time when thou shalt break and loosen his yoke from off thy neck. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 41.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Esau  was angry with Jacob because of the blessing, with which his father blessed him; and Esau said in his mind, Let the days of my father's  mourning draw nigh, that I may slay my brother Jacob.   
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 
\par }{\cs23\i\f1\fs24\insrsid3042872 Reader:}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The Prokeimenon, Psalm 107, in the 7}{\cs19\f35\fs32\super\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 th}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Tone:}{
\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872  
\par }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 Be Thou exalted above the heavens, O God, and Thy glory above all the earth.
\par 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 Stichos: }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Ready is my heart, O God, ready is my heart.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\pararsid16721749 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs21\b\fs36\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9070511 Deacon:}{\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid9070511  
