 To do justly and to speak truth, are more pleasing to God than the blood of sacrifices. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A high
 minded man is stout-hearted in his  pride; and the lamp of the wicked is sin. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 He that gathers treasures with a lying tongue pursues vanity on to the snares of death. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  Destruction shall lodge with the ungodly; for they refuse to do justly. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  To the forward God sends forward ways; for his works are pure  and right. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  It is better to dwell in a corner on the house-top, than in plastered rooms with unrighteousness, and in an open house. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The  soul of the ungodly shall not be pitied by any man. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 When an intemperate man is punished the simple becomes wiser: and a wise man  understanding will receive knowledge. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A righteous man understands the hearts of the ungodly: and despises the ungodly for their  wickedness. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  He that stops his ears
 from hearing the poor, himself also shall cry, and there shall be none to hear him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A secret gift  calms anger: but he that forbears to give stirs up strong wrath. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 It is the joy of the righteous to do judgment: but a holy man is  abominable with evil-doers. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A man that wanders out of the way of righteousness, shall rest in the congregation of giants. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A poor  man loves mirth, loving wine and oil in abundance; }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and a transgressor is the abomination of a righteous man. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 It is better to dwell in  a wilderness than with a quarrelsome and talkative and passionate woman. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A desirable treasure will rest on the mouth of the wise; but  foolish men will swallow it up. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The way of righteousness and mercy will find life and glory.   

\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
