 Cry aloud, and spare not; lift up thy voice as with a trumpet, and declare to my people their sins, and to the house of Jacob their  iniquities. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 They seek me day by day, and desire to know my ways, as a people that had done righteousness, and had not forsaken the  judgment of their God: they now ask of me righteous judgment, and desire to draw nigh to God, }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  saying, Why have we fasted, and thou  
regardest not? [why] have we afflicted our souls, and thou didst not know it? Nay, in the days of your fasts ye find your pleasures, and all  them that are under your power ye wound. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  If ye fast for quarrels and strifes, and smite the lowly with [your] fists, wherefore do ye fast  to me as [ye do] this day, so that your voice may be heard in crying? }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  I have not chosen this fast, nor [such] a day for a man to afflict his  soul; neither though thou shouldest bend down thy neck as a ring, and spread under 
thee sackcloth and ashes, neither thus shall ye call fast  acceptable. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 I have not chosen such a fast, saith the Lord; but do thou loose every burden of iniquity, do thou untie the knots of hard  bargains, set the bruised free, and cancel every unjust account. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Break thy bread to the hungry, and lead the unsheltered poor to thy  house: if thou seest one naked, clothe [him], and thou shalt not disregard the relations of thine own seed. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Then shall thy light break forth  as the morning, and thy health s
hall speedily spring forth: and thy righteousness shall go before thee, and the glory of God shall compass  thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Then shalt thou cry, and God shall hearken to thee; while thou art yet speaking he will say, Behold, I am here. If thou remove from  thee the band, and the stretching forth of the hands, and murmuring speech; }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and [if] thou give bread to the hungry from thy heart, and  satisfy the afflicted soul; then shall thy light spring up in darkness, and thy darkness [shall be] as noon-day: }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and t
hy God shall be with  thee continually, and thou shalt be satisfied according as thy soul desires; and thy bones shall be made fat, and shall be as a well watered  garden, and as a fountain [from] which the water has failed.   
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 
