 Desires kill the sluggard; for his hands do not choose to do anything. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 26.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 An ungodly man  entertains evil desires all the day: but the righteous is unsparingly merciful and compassionate. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 27.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 The sacrifices of the ungodly are  abomination to the Lord, for they offer them wickedly. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 28.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A false witness shall perish; but an ob
edient man will speak cautiously. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 29.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  An  ungodly man impudently withstands with his face; but the upright man himself understands his ways. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 30.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  There is no wisdom, there is no  courage, there is no counsel against the ungodly. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 31.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A horse is prepared for the day of battle; but help is of the Lord. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 1.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A fair name is  better than much wealth, and good favor is above silver and gold. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The rich and the poor meet together; but the Lord made them both.  }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  An intelligent man seeing a bad man severely punished is himself instructed, but fools pass by and are punished. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The fear of the Lord  is the offspring of wisdom, and wealth, and glory, and life. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Thistles and snares are in perverse ways; but he that keeps his soul will  refrain from them. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The rich wi
ll rule over the poor, and servants will lend to their own masters. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 He that sows wickedness shall reap  troubles; and shall fully receive the punishment of his deeds. God loves a cheerful and liberal man; but a man shall fully prove the folly of his  works. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 He that has pity on the poor shall himself be maintained; for he has given of his own bread to the poor. He that gives liberally  secures victory and honour; but he takes away the life of them that possess them. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Cast out a pestilent person from the council, and  strife shall go out with him; for when he sits in the council he dishonors all. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The Lord loves holy hearts, and all blameless persons are  acceptable with him: a king rules with his lips. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  But the eyes of the Lord preserve discretion; but the transgressor despises wise words.  }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 The sluggard makes excuses, and says, There is a lion in the ways, and murderers in the streets. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 The mouth of a transgressor is a  deep pit; and he that is hated of the Lord shall fall into it. Evil ways are before a man, and he does not like to turn away from them; but it is  needful to turn aside from a perverse and bad way. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Folly is attached to the heart of a child, but the rod and instruction are then far  from him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  He that oppresses the poor, increases his own substance, yet gives to the rich so as to make it less. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Incline thine ear to  the words of wise men: hear also my word, and apply thine heart, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 that thou mayest know that they are good: and if thou lay them to  heart, they shall also gladden thee on thy lips. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 That thy hope may be in the Lord, and he may make thy way known to thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And  do thou too repeatedly record them for thyself on the
 table of thine heart, for counsel and knowledge. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 I therefore teach thee truth, and  knowledge good to hear; that thou mayest answer words of truth to them that question thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 22.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Do no violence to the poor, for he is  needy: neither dishonor the helpless man in the gates. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 23.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 For the Lord will plead his cause, and thou shalt deliver thy soul in safety. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 24.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Be  not companion to a furious man; neither lodge with a passionate man: }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 25.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  lest thou learn of his ways, and get snares to thy soul. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 26.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  Become not surety from respect of a man's person. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 27.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For if those have not whence to give compensation, they will take the bed that is  under thee. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 28.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Remove not the old landmarks, which thy fathers placed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 29.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 It is fit that an observant man and one diligent in his business  should attend on kings, and not attend on slothful men. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 1.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 If thou sit to sup at the table of a prince, consider attentively the things set before  thee: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 and apply thine hand, knowing that it behooves thee to prepare such meats: but if thou art very insatiable, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 desire not his  provisions; for these belong to a false life. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  If thou art poor, measure not thyself with a rich man; but refrain thyself in thy wisdom. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  If  thou shouldest fix thine eye upon him, he will disappear; for wings like an eagle's are prepared for him, and he returns to the house of his  master. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Sup not with an envious man, neither desire thou his meats: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 so he eats and drinks as if any one should swallow a hair, and do  not bring him in to thyself, nor eat thy morsel with him: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 for he will vomit it up, and spoil thy fair words. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Say nothing in the ears of a  fool, lest at any time he sneer at thy wise words. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Remove not the ancient landmarks; and enter not upon the possession of the  fatherless: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  for the Lord is their redeemer; he is mighty, and will plead their cause with thee. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Apply thine heart to instruction, and  prepare thine ears for words of discretion. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Refrain not from chastening a child; for if thou beat him with the rod, he shall not die. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  For thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from death.   
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
