 So Israel departed, he and all he had, and came to the Well of the Oath, and offered a sacrifice to the God of his father Isaac. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And  God spoke to Israel in a vision of the night and said, "Jacob, Jacob." And he said, "What is it?" }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121   And God said to 
him, "I am the  God of your fathers. Do not be afraid to go down to Egypt, for I will make of you a great nation there, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 and I will go down with you to  Egypt, and ultimately I will go up with you, and Joseph will put his hands on your eyes." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Then Jac
ob arose from the Well of the Oath,  and Israel's sons put their father, their baggage and their wives on the wagons, which Joseph had sent to carry him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And they took their  belongings and all the possessions they had accumulated in Canaan and went to Egypt, Jacob and all his seed with him, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 his sons and  grandsons and his daughters and granddaughters. So he brought all his seed with him to Egypt.   
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 
