\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11692121 {\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Son, if thy heart be wise, thou shalt also gladden my heart; }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and thy lips shall converse with my lips, if they be right. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Let not  thine heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For if thou shouldest keep these things, thou shalt have  posterity; and thine hope shall not be removed. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Hear, my son, and be wise, and rightly direct the thoughts of thine heart. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Be not a  wine-bibber, neither continue long at feasts, and purchases of flesh: }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  for every drunkard and whore monger shall be poor; and every  sluggard shall clothe himself with tatters and ragged garments.  }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 22.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Hearken, my son, to thy father which begot thee, and despise not thy  mother because she is grown old. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 24.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A righteous father brings up his children well; and his soul rejoices over a wise son. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 25.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Let thy  father and thy mother rejoice over thee, and let her that bore thee be glad. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 26.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my  ways. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 27.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For a strange house is a vessel full of holes; and a strange well is narrow. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 28.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For such a one shall perish suddenly; and every  transgressor shall be cut off. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 29.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Who has woe? who trouble? who has quarrels? and who vexations and disputes? who has bruises  without a cause? whose eyes are livid? }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 30.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Are not those of them that stay long at wine? are not those of them that haunt the places where  banquets are? Be not drunk with wine; but converse with just men, and converse with them openly. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 31.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For if thou shouldest set thine eyes  on bowls and cups, thou shalt afterwards go more naked than a pestle. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 32.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 But at last such a one stretches himself out as one smitten by a  serpent, and venom is diffused through him as a horned serpent. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 33.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Whenever thine eyes shall be
hold a strange woman, then thy mouth  shall speak perverse things. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 34.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And thou shalt lie as in the midst of the sea, and as a pilot in a great storm. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 35.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And thou shalt say, They  smote me, and I was not pained; and they mocked me, and I knew it not: when
 will it be morning, that I may go and seek those with  whom I may go in company? }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 1.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  My son, envy not bad men, nor desire to be with them. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For their heart meditates falsehoods, and their  lips speak mischiefs. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  A house is built by wisdom, and is set up by understanding. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 By discretion the chambers are filled with all  precious and excellent wealth. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 A wise man is better than a strong man; and a man who has prudence than a large estate.   
\par }\pard\plain \s24\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs19\f35\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 Friday in the Sixth Week - At the Sixth Hour   
