\par Is 66:10-24}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121    
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\sl300\slmult1\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11692121 {\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Rejoice, O Jerusalem, and all ye that love her hold in her a general assembly: rejoice greatly with her, all that [now] mourn over her:  }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 that ye may such, and be satisfied with the breast of her consolation; that ye may milk out, and delight yourselves with the influx of her  glory. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 For thus saith the Lord, Behold, I turn toward them as a river of peace, and as a torrent bringing upon them in a flood the glory  of the Gentiles: their children shall be borne upon the shoulders, and comforted on the knees. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  As if his mother should comfort one, so  will I also comfort you; and ye shall be comforted in Jerusalem. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And ye shall see, and your heart shall rejoice, and your bones shall  thrive like grass: and the hand of the Lord shall be known to them that fear him, and he shall threaten the disobedient. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For, behold, the  Lord will come as fire, and his chariots as a storm, to render his vengeance with wrath, and his rebuke with a flame of fire. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For with  the fire of the Lord all the earth shall be judged, and all flesh with his sword: many shall be slain by the Lord. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 They that sanctify  themselves and purify themselves in the gardens, and eat swine's flesh in the porches, and the abominations, and the mouse, shall be  consumed together, saith the Lord. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And I [know] their works and their imagination. I am going to gather all nations and tongues; and  they shall come, and see my glory. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And I will leave a sign upon them, and I will send forth them that have escaped of them to the  nati
ons, to Tharsis, and Pud, and Lud, and Mosoch, and to Thobel, and to Greece, and to the isles afar off, to those who have not heard  my name, nor seen my glory; and they shall declare my glory among the Gentiles. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And they shall bring your brethren out 
of all nations  for a gift to the Lord with horses, and chariots, in litters [drawn by] mules with awnings, to the holy city Jerusalem, said the Lord, as  though the children of Israel should bring their sacrifices to me with psalms into the house of the 
Lord. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And I will take of them priests  and Levites, saith the Lord. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 22.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For as the new heaven and the new earth, which I make, remain before me, saith the Lord, so shall your  seed and your name continue. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 23.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And it shall come to pass from month to month, and from sabbath to sabbath, [that] all flesh shall come  to worship before me in Jerusalem, saith the Lord. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 24.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And they shall go forth, and see the carcasses of the men that have transgressed  against me: for their worm shall not die, and their fire s
hall shall not be quenched, and they shall be an abhorrence to all flesh.   
\par }\pard \s17\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 
\par }{\cs23\i\f1\fs24\insrsid3042872 Reader:}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  The Prokeimenon, Psalm 122, in the 6}{\cs19\f35\fs32\super\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 th}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Tone:}{
\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872  
\par }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par }{\cs20\i\f1\cf6\insrsid3042872 Stichos: }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Unto Thee have I lifted up mine eyes, unto Thee that dwellest in heaven.
\par 
