 And when Jacob finished commanding his sons, he drew up his feet into the bed and breathed his last and was added to his people. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 1.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  Then Joseph fell on his father's face and wept over him and kissed him. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 2.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Joseph commanded his servants the embalmers to embalm  his father. So the embalmers embalmed Israel. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 3.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And they fulfilled his fo
rty days, for such are the days required for embalming. And the  Egyptians mourned for him seventy days. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 4.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Now when the days of mourning were over, Joseph spoke to the princes of Pharaoh, saying,  "If I have found grace in your sight, speak for me in Pharaoh's hearing, saying, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 5.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid8206889\charrsid11692121 My}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 father adjured me, saying, "In the tomb I dug for  myself in the land of Canaan, there you shall bury me." Now therefore let me go up and bury my father, and I will return.'" }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 6.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And  Pharaoh said, "Go up and bury your father, just as he adjured you." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 7.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 So Joseph went up to bury his father, and there went up with him  all the servants of Pharaoh and the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land of Egypt, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 8.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  and all the household of Joseph and his  brothers and all his father's household and kindred. But they left their sheep and oxen in the land of Goshen. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 9.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  There went up also with  him both chariots and horses, and the encampment was very great. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 10.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Then they came to the threshing floor of Atad beyond the Jordan,  and they mourned for him with a very great and solemn lamentation. And he continued the mourning for his father seven days. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 11.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And the  inhabitants of the land of Canaan saw the mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, and they said, "This is a great mournin
g to the  Egyptians. For this reason one called its name the Mourning of Egypt, which is beyond the Jordan. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 12.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And so his sons did this for him  and buried him there. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 13.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  For his sons took him up to the land of Canaan and buried him in the double cave, wh
ich cave Abraham bought  for possession of a burying place from Ephron the Hittite opposite Mamre. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 14.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Then Joseph returned to Egypt, he and his brothers and  those who went up with him to bury his father. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 15.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Now when Joseph's brot
hers saw their father was dead, they said, "Possibly Joseph  may bear a grudge against us and exact vengeance on us for all the evils we did to him." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 16.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 So they came to Joseph, saying, "Your  father adjured us before he died, saying, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 17.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  }{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid8206889\charrsid11692121 Thus}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  you shall sa
y to Joseph, "Forgive them their injustice and their sins, because they did  you evil."' Now therefore, forgive the injustice of the servants of your father's God." And Joseph wept while they were speaking to  him. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 18.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And coming near him they said, "We here are your servants." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 19.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 Then Joseph said to them, "Do not fear, for I am God's. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 20.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
  You took counsel against me for evil, but God took counsel on my behalf for good, that it might happen as today, that many people might  be nourished." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 21.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 He also said to them, "Do not fear. I will nourish you and your households." Thus he comforted them and spoke to  their heart. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 22.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 So Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his brothers, and all the household of his father. And Joseph lived one hundred and ten  years. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 23.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  And 
he saw Ephraim's children to the third generation, and the sons of Machir, Manasseh's son, were also brought up on  Joseph's lap. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 24.}{\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
 And Joseph spoke to his brothers, saying, "I am about to die, but God will assuredly visit you and will bring you up  from this land to the land God swore to our fathers, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 25.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  Then Joseph adjured the sons of Israel, saying, "In  the visitation wherewith God will visit you, you must carry up my bones with you from here." }{\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 26.}{
\cs19\f35\fs32\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121  So Joseph died being one hundred and  ten years old, and they embalmed him and put him in a coffin in Egypt.   
\par }\pard \s17\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs16\insrsid3042872\charrsid11692121 
